1. Created a namespace with ckad-prep

YAML :

apiVersion: v1
kind: Namespace
metadata:
	name: ckad-prep
	labels:
		environment: ckad
		
Verify : kubectl get ns
			
2. Created a pod under the ckad-prep namespace 

YAML:

apiVersion: v1
kind: Pod
metadata:
  name: mypod 
  namespace: ckad-prep
spec:
  containers:
  - name: nginx
    image: nginx:1.15.12
    ports:
    - containerPort: 80
	
Verify : kubectl get pods --namespace=ckad-prep

3. Pod is not running due to image pull pack as the version is not correct 

So, modified the YAML and applied 

mypod   Running

4. Verify container status:

kubectl describe pod mypod -n ckad-prep

5. Log into the Container and Run ls

kubectl exec -it mypod -n ckad-prep -- /bin/bash
ls

6. Retrieve the IP Address of Pod mypod

kubectl get pod mypod -n ckad-prep -o wide

7. Run a Temporary BusyBox Pod and Test Connectivity

kubectl run busybox --rm -it \
--image=busybox \
--namespace=ckad-prep \
-- /bin/sh

8. Render Logs of Pod mypod

kubectl logs mypod -n ckad-prep

9. Delete the Pod and Namespace

kubectl delete pod mypod -n ckad-prep
